      • newClassifier

        public static IClassifier<double[]> newClassifier(String classifierSpec,
                                                  Map<String,?> bindings)
                                           throws AISPException
        Parse the specification to provide a classifier.
        Parameters:
        classifierSpec - a factory specification in the form of <type>:<type-specific builder content>. The following types are supported
        • 'js' builder content is a javascript string to be used by a JScriptClassifierFactory.
        • 'jsfile' builder content is the name of a file containing java script or java script template to be used by JScriptClassifierFactory.
        • empty then we fall over to #newBuiltInClassifier(String, String). See it for details.
        bindings - provides values to fill into java script templates if used to match the given classifier spec. may be null.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        AISPException - if unrecognized classifierSpec is given.
        See Also:
        JScriptClassifierFactory}

      • newBuiltInClassifier

        public static IClassifier<double[]> newBuiltInClassifier(String modelTypeName,
                                                         Map<String,? extends Object> bindings)
                                                  throws AISPException
        Convert a string and the name of a training label into an IClassifier instance. Use this instread of newClassifier(String, Map) when you don't want to support the other reference types such as "jsfile:". Support type names are javascript file names found in the classpath in this package. See getModelSpecifications() for the complete list.
        Parameters:
        modelTypeName -
        bindings - applied to the template if found for the give modelTypeName. May be null.
        Returns:
        never null
        Throws:
        AISPException - if unrecognized type name is given.

      • getModelSpecifications

        public static Map<String,JavaScriptFactories.InstanceSpecification> getModelSpecifications()
        Get this list of all model specifications known to this factory. This is the base names of all javascript files (ending with .js or .jsyt) found in the same package as this class.
        Returns:
        never null. Basenames of javascript resources files in the same package as this class anywhere on the classpath.
